org.openimaj.image.feature.local.keypoints.quantised

Class QuantisedKeypoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.feature.local.quantised.QuantisedLocalFeature<KeypointLocation>
      • org.openimaj.image.feature.local.keypoints.quantised.QuantisedKeypoint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FeatureVectorProvider<IntFV>, LocalFeature<KeypointLocation,IntFV>, LocalFeatureVectorProvider<KeypointLocation,IntFV>, LocationProvider<KeypointLocation>, Readable, ReadableASCII, ReadableBinary, ReadWriteable, Writeable, WriteableASCII, WriteableBinary, Coordinate, Point2d

    public class QuantisedKeypoint
extends QuantisedLocalFeature<KeypointLocation>
implements Point2d
    A QuantisedKeypoint is a QuantisedLocalFeature with its location described by a KeypointLocation. It is the quantised equivalent to a Keypoint, with the feature vector replaced by a single integer assignment.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
